latestPosts.caption:
😭😭!! thank YOU for making this possible. 
we share a passion for fitness, but what truly connects us is the path to self-improvement. And I know from experience that it can be a lonely journey to be on.. 

Having to say no to things you previously would have said yes to, or not living up to other people’s expectations from you (anymore). 

Please never forget that there are people out there who will root for you and who will have your back. People like yourself who have shown support in another woman - me. 

Magic happens when women support women. 

Just finished my first event to celebrate this launch of my first cover (CAN’T BELIEVE I’M SAYING THIS) and my heart is so full😭😭 I’ll continue doing my best to connect our community in real life. thank you from the bottom of my heart❤️❤️❤️❤️ whether it’s by leaving a comment, engaging with any of my content or leaving a like - your support made this possible. 

thank you @womenshealthnl for asking me to be on the cover. I’m so honored❤️

latestPosts.caption: what I ate today for fat loss

what I wish I knew when I started training - I almost over emphasized training details and underestimated the importance of food, especially for us women. and sleep. sleep is key for recovery abilities. that being said, shred has been going good! lots of patience and consistency aka the boring stuff aka the stuff that gets you results 🤫😌

a killller lower ab workout 🤫🤫 
10 x ab circles clockwise 
10 x ab circles anti-clockwise 
12 x v-ups
12 x in & out 
10 x hip lifts 
10 x sprinter crunch (per side)
12 x incline leg raise 
12 x toe touches 

repeat twice / rest when needed

trying to get to that final boss level with pull ups where the rest of your body isn’t moving an inch 😭 

back & biceps keeping it simple & to the golden standards: 

1. pull ups 4 x 6-8 (use a resistance band if you cannot do 6-8) alternatively you can do a lat pulldown or any other vertical pull
2. bent over barbell row 4 x 8-10 
3. rear delt fly on the cable (10 / 10 variation) 3 x 12-15 per side 
4. behind the body cable curls 3 x 10-12 per side
